{{Quote|You are as observant as we recall, Princess. Others are not usually observant enough to perceive the Chronicle.|[[Raynar Thul|UnuThul]] to [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]]|<ref name="Dark Nest I: The Joiner King">''[[Dark Nest I: The Joiner King]]''</ref>}}
The '''Chronicle''' was colorful mosaics that decorated the interior of the [[Prime Chamber]] in the [[Killik/Legends|Killik]] [[The Colony|Colony]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Yoggoy]]. According to [[Mara Jade Skywalker]], one could not look directly at the Chronicle to obtain its details, the Chronicle was like one of those air-jellies on [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]], it only showed up when one looked away.

It detailed the crash of the ''[[Tachyon Flier]]'' on Yoggoy; the Killiks waiting [[Raynar Thul]] to die; how Raynar touched the Killiks in [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] which made the insects to care for him; the healing and transformation of Raynar to a [[Joiner]]; the change of the [[Yoggoy (Hive)|Yoggoy nest]] and the creation of the [[Unu]] hive; and finally how the Colony defeated a rebelling nest.

When the [[Skywalker family/Legends|Skywalker couple]], the [[Solo family/Legends|Solo couple]] and [[Saba Sebatyne]] went to Yoggoy to investigate the disappearance of [[Myrkr strike team]] survivors in [[35 ABY/Legends|35 ABY]], [[Raynar Thul|UnuThul]] showed the Chronicle to the group when [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] asked for the details.

The Chronicle was presumed abandoned with the Prime Chamber after the [[Qoribu Truce]].

